# Spotify Top Tracks App

A full-stack Node.js application that allows users to authenticate via Spotify OAuth, view their top 5 most-played tracks, and receive personalized advice or suggestions based on their music preferences.

---

## Features

- **Spotify OAuth Login** using Authorization Code Flow
- **Top 5 Tracks API** using Spotify Web API (`/me/top/tracks`)
- **Advice API Integration** to offer music-based suggestions (`https://api.adviceslip.com/advice`)
- Clean separation of frontend & backend
- Token and session management in localStorage

---

## Tech Stack

- **Backend:** Node.js, Express.js
- **OAuth:** Spotify Authorization Code Flow
- **APIs Used:** Spotify Web API, Custom Advice API
- **Environment:** dotenv, axios, nodemon

---
## Running the App

### 1. Install Dependencies

Make sure you're in the project root, then run:

```bash
npm install
npm run dev <`starts the nodemon`>
npm start without Nodemon
